ğŸ”· Question: What is the Main Method in C#?
Answer:  
â€¢ `Main()` is the entry point and exit point of a C# application  
â€¢ It is the first method that runs when the program starts  
â€¢ The .NET compiler looks for `Main()` to begin execution  
â€¢ You can have multiple `Main()` methods in different classes, but only one is used to start the program  
â€¢ `Main()` can take input using `string[] args` (used for command-line arguments)

ğŸ”¸ Structure of Main Method:
class Program  
{  
    public static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
        // code starts running from here  
    }  
}

ğŸŸ¢ Easy to speak:  
"Main method is where the program starts and ends.  
It tells the computer, 'Start running code from here.'  
Only one Main method is the real starting point.  
We can also pass inputs to it if needed."


