ğŸ”· Question: What is `void` and `static` keyword?
Answer:
â€¢ void â†’ It means the method does NOT return any value  
â€¢ Used when we just want to perform actions, not send any result back  
â€¢ In Main(), we use void because no value is returned to the system  

â€¢ static â†’ It means the method belongs to the CLASS itself, not to any object  
â€¢ This allows the method to be called WITHOUT creating an object  
â€¢ The Main() method is static so the program can start directly from it

ğŸ”¸ Structure Example:
class Program  
{  
    public static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
        // statements  
    }  
}


